%div#content
  %div.col.one
    %section.section
      %h1 Meetups
      %p Our meetups are open to all experience levels, from total novices to expert Rubyists.

      .vevent
        %h2.summary BR-5: Shipping It: Optimising Application Deployment

        %h3.when-icon.icon When?
        %p
          %span.dtstart
            - date_string = '2012-11-6'
            - date = Date.parse date_string
            %abbr.value{ :title => "#{date_string}" } #{date.strftime("#{date.day.ordinalize} %B, %Y")}
            %span.value 6:30pm

        %h3.where-icon.icon
          Where?
          %a.get-directions{ :href => "https://maps.google.com/maps?f=d&source=s_d&saddr=&hl=en&ie=UTF8&layer=c&daddr=54.599297,-5.9242997", :title => "Examtime"} Get Directions
          
        %p.location
          Examtime Limited
          %br
          1st Floor, 83-85 Victoria Street, Belfast, BT1 4PB

        %h3.what-icon.icon What?
        %p.description
          So, you've built a great product. Now you have to ship it! Getting your code in front of users is the last hurdle, but gone are the days of having to actually mail it... but why stop there! Tonight's talks will feature discussion on the current state of Ruby deployment and just how fast we can reach our users.

        %h4 Zero Downtime Deployments with Unicorn
        %p.description
          David Kennedy of <a href="http://www.examtime.com/">Examtime</a> will present about how they have improved their infrastructure to allow for zero downtime deployments.</p>

        %h4 Shipping It
        %p.description 
          David Rice of <a href="http://rumblelabs.com">Rumble Labs</a> will present about some strategies used to improve efficiency and reliability of application deployment, by harnessing the power of robots. </p>

        %a.url.cta{:href=> "http://digitalcircle.org/events/belfast-ruby-shipping-it-optimising-application-deployment"} Attend Meetup >
